<h2><b>ADULTS</b></h2>
<h4><a href="/life-learning/spiritual-life-classes/study-in-the-book-of-ephesians/">STUDY IN THE BOOK OF EPHESIANS</a></h4>
<p><strong><em>7:00-8:30 PM in the Chapel</em></strong><br />How does God think about you?&nbsp;What does Jesus want you to do with your life? How can you overcome negative influences each day? If you want to understand your identity in Christ, there&rsquo;s no better place to start than the book of Ephesians&mdash;a letter written by Paul to a group of people who had these same questions. Rev. Rod and Huyen Rider pulls from biblical, historical, and scholarly sources to bring us surprising insights from the book of Ephesians.</p>
<h4><b><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/life-learning/spiritual-life-classes/ladies-tuesday-am-bible-study/">LADIES' BIBLE STUDY</a></b></h4>
<p><em><strong>7:00-8:30 PM in the Hospitality Center</strong></em><br />Join us on Tuesday mornings or Wednesday evenings for&nbsp;Experiencing God&nbsp;by Henry Blackaby &amp; Claude King. This study centers around knowing and doing the will of God. You are invited to experience God in an intimate love relationship through which He reveals His will, His ways and His work. The cost is $25 per person which covers your workbook and childcare expenses for the duration of the study.</p>
<h4><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/get-connected/men/mens-bible-studies/"><b>MEN'S BIBLE STUDY</b></a></h4>
<p><strong><em>7:00-8:30 PM in Room 228</em></strong><br /> <em>The Coming Economic Armageddon: What Bible Prophecy Warns about the New Global Economy&nbsp;</em>by David Jeremiah. Never before have we read such jarring headlines, distressing news analyses, or dire predictions concerning the world's financial future. The American housing market - or, more sentimentally, the American dream - began to collapse in 2006, taking with it large chunks of the global financial system. Millions of jobs worldwide have vanished forever. Did Bible prophecy predict this catastrophe? Are there biblical clues to how soon, if ever, a viable, long-term recovery can be sustained? Is the financial collapse just one of several signs that we are living in the final days of Earth's history in The Coming Economic Armageddon, David Jeremiah says we can know the meaning behind what we see in the daily news - and understand and prepare for living in the New Global Economy.</p>
<p><strong> </strong></p>
<h4><strong><b><a href="/ministries/adult-education/love-and-logic-parenting-classes/becoming-love-and-logic-parent/">BECOMING A LOVE &amp; LOGIC PARENT</a><br /></b></strong></h4>
<p><strong><strong><em>7:00-8:30 PM in Rooms 229-230</em></strong><br />Material Fee: $20.00 for individual; $35.00 for couple<br /></strong>The key to effective parenting is discovering what motivates your child to respond the way he or she does. You will walk away with 9 essential parenting skills that are guaranteed to work! Class includes a workbook, binder notebook, small group interaction, large group lecture, and DVD presentation with Dr. Charles Fay, Jim Fay, and Dr. Foster Clines! Led by Amy Slater.</p>
<h4><strong><b><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/get-connected/music-and-worship/portland-christian-center-choir/">PORTLAND CHRISTIAN CENTER CHOIR</a><br /></b></strong></h4>
<p><strong><em>7:00-8:30 PM in the Choir Room</em></strong><br /> The Portland Christian Center Choir is open periodically for new members. If you are at least 18 years of age, and have music experience, we'd love to have you audition to join us!</p>
<hr />
<h2><strong><b><b>YOUTH</b></b></strong></h2>
<h4><strong><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/get-connected/music-and-worship/student-choirs/">WITNESS: MIDDLE SCHOOL CHOIR (GRADES 6-8)</a></strong></h4>
<p><strong><em>6:00-7:00 PM in Room 221</em></strong><br />This fun choir is open to all Middle School students. Witness participates in many fun music projects and activities throughout the year, including an annual choir our every June, as well  as performing for 15,000 people during the annual Portland's Christmas  Celebration concerts.</p>
<h4><strong><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/get-connected/music-and-worship/student-choirs/">PRIORITY: HIGH SCHOOL AND COLLEGE CHOIR (GRADE 9 TO AGE 20)</a></strong></h4>
<p><strong><em>6:00-7:00 PM in the Choir Room</em></strong><br />This year, Priority begins its 22nd season of ministry at Portland  Christian Center! This dynamic choir is open to all High School and  College students (up to age 20). We'd love to have you join us! We have an incredible  year planned, including an awesome 10 day summer tour in June!</p>
<h4><strong><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/get-connected/middle-school/intensify-the-revolution/">REVOLUTION: MIDDLE SCHOOL (GRADES 6-8)</a></strong></h4>
<p><strong><em>7:00-8:30 PM in the Fireside Room</em></strong><br /> Revolution is a safe place to meet new friends and have lots of fun  together. We shatter the &ldquo;church is boring&rdquo; stereotype and give you tons  of reasons to get connected and grow in Jesus! The best part is that we  engage you and challenge you to become the person who God has created you to be.</p>
<h4><strong><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/get-connected/high-school/">UNVEILED: HIGH SCHOOL (GRADES 9-12)</a></strong></h4>
<p><em><strong>7:00-8:30 PM in the Youth Center</strong></em><br />We are a group of young people who are passionate about discovering who we are, who God is, and what this life is all about. 2 Corinthians 3:16-18 tells us that when we turn to Christ, the veil is taken away, and we are able to see clearly for the first time. That&rsquo;s when the adventure of living for God begins! So come check out what&rsquo;s going on at Unveiled!</p>
<hr />
<h2><b><b>CHILDREN</b></b></h2>
<h4><strong><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/kidsmusic/">KIDS PRAISE COMPANY! - CHILDREN 1ST-5TH GRADES</a></strong></h4>
<p><em><strong>6:00-7:00 PM IN ROOMS 217-219 Beginning October 5th</strong></em><br /> Kids, join us for the most awesome children's choir on the planet -  Kids Praise Company! This super fun and musically educational program is for all kids from 1st-5th grades. Join us as we have tons of fun launching into our spring musical. This fully staged, costumed and coreographed event is sure to be one of the highlights of your year! You don't want to miss it!!</p>
<h4><strong><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/get-connected/children/midweek-programs/nursery/">NURSERY CARE - CHILDREN BIRTH-AGE 2</a></strong></h4>
<p><em><strong>6:30-8:30 PM in the Nursery</strong></em><br /> We have loving, CPR-trained, background checked nursery workers to provide tender care to your little ones while mom and dad attend a class or workshop.</p>
<h4><strong><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/get-connected/children/midweek-programs/preschool/">RAINBOWS CLUB - CHILDREN AGE 3-PRE K</a></strong></h4>
<p><em><strong>7:00-8:30 PM</strong></em>, 100 Wing<br /> Join us each week for a fun adventure aboard Noah's Ark! We earn a different animal  badge each month by attending class, memorizing a bible verse and doing  fun worksheets and crafts.</p>
<h4><strong><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/get-connected/children/midweek-programs/elementary/">ROYAL RANGERS - BOYS K-5TH GRADE</a></strong></h4>
<p><strong><em>7:00-8:30 PM</em></strong>, 200 Wing<br /> Royal Rangers offers character and servant leadership education to boys and young men in a highly relational,fun,and interactive environment, similar to Boy Scouts.</p>
<h4><strong><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/get-connected/children/midweek-programs/elementary/">M'S GIRLS CLUB - GIRLS K-5TH GRADE</a></strong></h4>
<p><strong><em>7:00-8:30 PM</em></strong>, 200 Wing<br />M's Club guides girls in their relationship with Jesus  through an environment of support, friendship, crafts and activities, while helping them develop their unique gifts and abilities.</p>
